.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH manta-cli-apply-hardware-cluster 1  "cluster " 
.SH NAME
manta\-cli\-apply\-hardware\-cluster \- [experimental] Rescale a cluster\*(Aqs hardware allocation
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmanta\-cli apply hardware cluster\fR <\fB\-P\fR|\fB\-\-pattern\fR> <\fB\-t\fR|\fB\-\-target\-cluster\fR> <\fB\-p\fR|\fB\-\-parent\-cluster\fR> [\fB\-d\fR|\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-c\fR|\fB\-\-create\-target\-hsm\-group\fR] [\fB\-D\fR|\fB\-\-delete\-empty\-parent\-hsm\-group\fR] [\fB\-u\fR|\fB\-\-unpin\-nodes\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
[experimental] Upscale or downscale a cluster by specifying a hardware component pattern.
.PP
If the cluster does not exist it will be created; otherwise its node assignment is updated.
.PP
Pattern format: <component>:<quantity>[:<component>:<quantity>...]
eg: \*(Aqa100:12:epyc:5\*(Aq  — assign nodes with 12 A100 GPUs and 5 EPYC CPUs total
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-P\fR, \fB\-\-pattern\fR \fI<PATTERN>\fR
Hardware pattern: <component>:<qty>[:<component>:<qty>...].
eg: \*(Aqa100:12:epyc:5\*(Aq
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-target\-cluster\fR \fI<TARGET_CLUSTER_NAME>\fR
Cluster to rescale
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-parent\-cluster\fR \fI<PARENT_CLUSTER_NAME>\fR
Cluster that donates or receives the redistributed nodes
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Simulate the operation without making changes
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-create\-target\-hsm\-group\fR
Create the target cluster if it does not exist
.TP
\fB\-D\fR, \fB\-\-delete\-empty\-parent\-hsm\-group\fR
Delete the parent cluster if empty after this operation
.TP
\fB\-u\fR, \fB\-\-unpin\-nodes\fR
Allow any available nodes to be selected
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
